<!-- ===== OVERVIEW ===== -->
<div class="tab-panel active" id="tab-overview">
  <div class="section">
    <div class="sh"><span class="si">🧠</span><span class="st">Core Thesis</span></div>
    <div class="card hi">
      <div class="ct">What This Is</div>
      <ul class="bl">
        <li><strong>Claude Code</strong> is a coding agent that runs in your terminal or desktop app — you describe what you want built, it writes code, runs it, fixes errors, and ships it</li>
        <li><strong>No coding knowledge required</strong> — but you need to know exactly what you want before you ask</li>
        <li><strong>Think of it as a developer</strong> who works instantly and free, but needs clear briefs every time</li>
        <li><strong>The CLAUDE.md file</strong> is the single biggest leverage point — build it once, every session reads it automatically</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="sh"><span class="si">🎯</span><span class="st">NCP Priority Order</span></div>
    <div class="pri high"><div class="plab">Priority 1</div><div class="pb"><strong>Ankle Program page</strong> — next product, build first</div></div>
    <div class="pri high"><div class="plab">Priority 2</div><div class="pb"><strong>CLAUDE.md</strong> — permanent session briefing (already built June 2026)</div></div>
    <div class="pri mod"><div class="plab">Priority 3</div><div class="pb"><strong>Instagram audit setup</strong> — Windsor.ai or Claude in Chrome</div></div>
    <div class="pri mod"><div class="plab">Priority 4</div><div class="pb"><strong>Content pipeline tool</strong> — trending topics + competitor dashboard</div></div>
    <div class="pri low"><div class="plab">Ongoing</div><div class="pb"><strong>Clinical report generators</strong> — 1-to-1, combine, NCP combine</div></div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="sh"><span class="si">⚡</span><span class="st">Key Principles</span></div>
    <ul class="bl">
      <li><strong>Context degrades over time</strong> — the longer the session, the worse Claude performs; keep sessions short and focused</li>
      <li><strong>One task per session</strong> — don't chain multiple builds; finish one, start fresh</li>
      <li><strong>Plan before code</strong> — use plan mode for anything touching multiple files; explore first, plan second, build third</li>
      <li><strong>Verify everything</strong> — ask Claude to run checks on its own output; never ship without a verification step</li>
      <li><strong>HANDOFF.md</strong> — before ending any long session, write what was tried, what worked, what didn't, what's next</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="pnotes">
    <span class="pnlab">📝 Your Notes — Overview</span>
    <textarea id="pn-overview" placeholder="Add your own notes here…" oninput="saveNote('overview')"></textarea>
    <div class="psaved" id="sv-overview">Saved ✓</div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ===== WHAT CLAUDE CODE IS ===== -->
<div class="tab-panel" id="tab-whatitis">
  <div class="section">
    <div class="sh"><span class="si">🤖</span><span class="st">How It Works</span></div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="ct">The Agentic Loop</div>
      <ul class="bl">
        <li><strong>Gather context</strong> — reads your files, understands your codebase</li>
        <li><strong>Take action</strong> — writes code, runs commands, edits files</li>
        <li><strong>Verify results</strong> — runs tests, checks output, fixes errors</li>
        <li><strong>Repeats</strong> — cycles until task is done or you redirect it</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="ct">Built-in Tools</div>
      <ul class="bl">
        <li><strong>File operations</strong> — read, edit, create, rename files</li>
        <li><strong>Search</strong> — find files by pattern, search content, explore codebases</li>
        <li><strong>Execution</strong> — run shell commands, start servers, run tests, use git</li>
        <li><strong>Web</strong> — search the web, fetch documentation, look up errors</li>
        <li><strong>Browser</strong> — Claude in Chrome for visual audits and form interactions</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="sh"><span class="si">📍</span><span class="st">Access Points</span></div>
    <ul class="bl">
      <li><strong>Claude Desktop app</strong> — primary interface (Harry has this installed)</li>
      <li><strong>Claude in Chrome</strong> — browser extension for Instagram/competitor audits (Harry has this)</li>
      <li><strong>Terminal</strong> — type <code>claude</code> in any project folder to start</li>
      <li><strong>VS Code / JetBrains</strong> — IDE integrations available if needed later</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="sh"><span class="si">⚠️</span><span class="st">Key Constraint</span></div>
    <div class="card warn">
      <div class="ct">Context Window Fills Fast</div>
      <ul class="bl">
        <li><strong>Performance degrades</strong> as context fills — at <span class="num">256K tokens</span> efficiency is ~<span class="num">91%</span>, at <span class="num">1M tokens</span> it drops to <span class="num">65–78%</span></li>
        <li><strong>Clear at 20–25%</strong> of context window — don't wait until it's full</li>
        <li><strong>/clear</strong> resets context completely; <strong>/compact</strong> summarises and compresses</li>
        <li><strong>Fresh sessions outperform long ones</strong> — start new conversations for new tasks</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="pnotes">
    <span class="pnlab">📝 Your Notes — What Claude Code Is</span>
    <textarea id="pn-whatitis" placeholder="Add your own notes here…" oninput="saveNote('whatitis')"></textarea>
    <div class="psaved" id="sv-whatitis">Saved ✓</div>
  </div>
</div>

