<!-- ===== SETUP PROTOCOL ===== -->
<div class="tab-panel" id="tab-setup">
  <div class="section">
    <div class="sh"><span class="si">🛠</span><span class="st">Week-by-Week Setup</span></div>

    <div class="proto">
      <div class="pn">WEEK 1 — GET ORIENTED</div>
      <ul class="bl">
        <li><strong>Step 1:</strong> Open Claude Code desktop app</li>
        <li><strong>Step 2:</strong> Place <code>CLAUDE.md</code> at <code>~/.claude/CLAUDE.md</code> (the file built June 2026)</li>
        <li><strong>Step 3:</strong> Open a terminal in any project folder and run <code>claude</code> to start a session</li>
        <li><strong>Step 4:</strong> Pick ONE small build — Ankle Program product page is the recommended first task</li>
        <li><strong>Pass:</strong> Claude reads your CLAUDE.md automatically, knows your brand, asks no context questions</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="proto">
      <div class="pn">WEEK 2 — FIRST REAL BUILD</div>
      <ul class="bl">
        <li><strong>Task:</strong> Build the Ankle Program landing page</li>
        <li><strong>Brief format:</strong> Write <span class="num">3–5</span> sentences describing exactly what you want before opening Claude Code</li>
        <li><strong>Use plan mode:</strong> Shift+Tab to enter plan mode — Claude plans before it builds</li>
        <li><strong>Verify:</strong> Ask Claude to screenshot the result and check it against the brief</li>
        <li><strong>Git:</strong> Ask Claude to commit with a descriptive message after each working build</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="proto">
      <div class="pn">WEEK 3 — INSTAGRAM AUDIT</div>
      <ul class="bl">
        <li><strong>Option A (quick):</strong> Claude in Chrome already installed — log into Instagram in Chrome, enable Claude in Chrome in a new chat, run audit prompts</li>
        <li><strong>Option B (deep):</strong> Set up Windsor.ai at onboard.windsor.ai, connect Instagram, add Windsor connector to Claude, run full API audit</li>
        <li><strong>Recommended start:</strong> Chrome first, Windsor second</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="proto">
      <div class="pn">WEEK 4+ — CONTENT PIPELINE TOOL</div>
      <ul class="bl">
        <li><strong>Build:</strong> Dashboard pulling trending topics, competitor activity, outputs NCP Idea Briefs</li>
        <li><strong>Integration:</strong> Connects to Notion Content Flow database (ID: <span class="num">1170f8bb-702f-8156-9912-d1737d19b608</span>)</li>
        <li><strong>Output format:</strong> Idea Brief cards → push to Notion → Harry flips to Research → Agent B scripts</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="sh"><span class="si">📋</span><span class="st">Essential Commands</span></div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="ct">Commands to Know</div>
      <ul class="bl">
        <li><strong>/init</strong> — scan a project folder and generate a CLAUDE.md for it automatically</li>
        <li><strong>/clear</strong> — reset context window between unrelated tasks</li>
        <li><strong>/compact</strong> — summarise conversation to free space while preserving key decisions</li>
        <li><strong>/compact [focus]</strong> — e.g. <code>/compact focus on the API changes</code></li>
        <li><strong>/status line</strong> — set up a status bar showing model, directory, context % used</li>
        <li><strong>Shift+Tab</strong> — cycle between modes (default → plan mode → auto)</li>
        <li><strong>Esc</strong> — stop Claude mid-action, context preserved, can redirect</li>
        <li><strong>Esc+Esc or /rewind</strong> — roll back to a previous conversation checkpoint</li>
        <li><strong>ultra think</strong> — type this in your prompt for complex architecture decisions (uses ~<span class="num">32K</span> extra tokens)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="ct">HANDOFF.md Pattern</div>
      <ul class="bl">
        <li><strong>When to write:</strong> before ending any long or incomplete session</li>
        <li><strong>What to include:</strong> what was tried, what worked, what didn't, what's next</li>
        <li><strong>How to use:</strong> start fresh session, load HANDOFF.md path only — nothing else</li>
        <li><strong>Why:</strong> preserves progress without polluting the new session's context</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

